				<div id="section-sub-ad" data-cb-ad-id="section-sub-ad"></div>
				<section class="article-list">
					<header class="rail-article-author">
  <h2 class="rail-article-brand-title">Richard Corliss</h2>
  <img class="rail-article-author-photo" src="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/01/71233c5a174d2a77a4b43d4ad39c3968.jpg?w=100&amp;h=100&amp;crop=1" />
  <p class="rail-article-summary-paragraph">Richard Corliss joined TIME in 1980 as a movie critic, a position he still holds. Before TIME, he wrote for <i>National Review</i>, <i>New Times</i>, <i>Maclean’s of Canada</i> and <i>SoHo Weekly News</i>. He was also editor for <i>Film Comment</i> from 1970 to 1990. Corliss is the author of the books <i>Talking Pictures</i>, a study of Hollywood screenwriters, and <i>Greta Garbo</i> (both 1974). In 1994 he wrote a study of the novel and film <i>Lolita</i>. Corliss holds a B.A. from Saint Joseph’s College in Philadelphia and an M.S. in film studies from Columbia University. He lives in New York City with his wife, Mary.</p>
  
  
  
